This would mean that `(⋃ N, ⋃ (hN : N ∈ D), B N hN) \ {x} = ∅`.

To show this, we need to prove that any element `y` in `S = ⋃ N, ⋃ (hN : N ∈ D), B N hN` must be equal to `x`.

